data.text: 3. War Paint in 2017, we’d waited seven songs and then suddenly Patti LuPone and Christine Ebersole harmonise for the first time while singing If I’d Been A Man. I grab @hollylottie88's arm, my wig just flew off, I’ve never heard anything so gorgeous in my life up to that point.
2. Imelda Staunton reaching the climax of Everything’s Coming Up Roses in Gypsy, Her arms shaking with pure determination, every hair on my body was standing on end.
